{
  "stem": "25639.5",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And from there, you come back, and she'll make her way back.' And that's what I did, and I went back to the barrack and was reunited with my mother again.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I'd like to share with you another daily-- almost daily event, in Auschwitz-Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think you now understand how we-- each morning, we had to walk through different electric wire fences-- the gates through them-- to-- to go to work.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "At a certain point, just before we entered the electric wire fence gate into the forested area, there would be, very often, important visitors. 'Important' visitors.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Heinrich Himmler, the head of the SS, the head of the Gestapo and the secret police, head of all the concentration camps, came one day with Hermann Goring, who was the head of the German Air Force.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And next to Hitler, he was the most powerful man in Germany.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As we were counted off right there, before entering into the forested area where the death factory really is, there was Goring, and there was Himmler.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I couldn't believe my eyes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I saw pictures of them in newspapers, so I recognized Himmler particularly, with his little rim-wire glasses.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I was in the outer file, nearest him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we were marching to work.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And as I reached close to him, he gave me a kick in the behind with his boot.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It didn't hurt.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's just that I sometimes wonder, didn't he have anything better to do?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] Another event I'd like to talk about.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This very same place, just before we entered the forested area-- very often, we would have a little ensemble, a little small orchestra, playing music.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
